short_description: This function gives score according to generalized linear model.
long_description: This function gives score according to generalized linear model.

input_tables.description: Specifies the table containing the input data.

argument_clauses.name: ModelTable
argument_clauses.description: Specifies the model table from glm for the prediction

argument_clauses.name: Accumulate
argument_clauses.description: Specifies a comma-separated list of the names of the columns in the input table

argument_clauses.name: Family
argument_clauses.description: Specifies the glm family and the default value is 'BINOMIAL' The permitted input values are [LOGISTIC, BINOMIAL, POISSON, GAUSSIAN, GAMMA, INVERSE_GAUSSIAN, NEGATIVE_BINOMIAL]. The default value is BINOMIAL.

argument_clauses.name: Link
argument_clauses.description: Specifies the canonical link function and the default value is 'CANONICAL' The permitted input values are [CANONICAL, IDENTITY, INVERSE, LOG, COMPLEMENTARY_LOG_LOG, SQUARE_ROOT, INVERSE_MU_SQUARED, LOGIT, PROBIT, CAUCHIT]. The default value is CANONICAL.
